Business Brief -- Video Lottery Technologies Inc.:
   Gaming Equipment Maker
   To Buy Control Data Unit
The Bozeman, Mont., manufacturer of video gaming equipment
said the planned purchase would strengthen its position in
the lottery industry. In 1991, Video Lottery posted revenue
of $31 million, while the Control Data division reported $114
million in sales.
   The announcement sent Video Lottery shares up $3 to close
at $31.75 in over-the-counter trading; in Big Board trading,
Control Data shares rose $1.50 to close at $12.50.
   Control Data, a Minneapolis information services and
computer company, said the sale will allow it to "employ
additional assets in service markets more consistent with our
skills base," including employer services and market
research.